Moleskine Wine Journal
List.Description:
Moleskine hardcover journals are legendary and they've created this wine journal to include everything you need to keep track of your wine and wine tastings. Journal includes 6 theme-based sections, as well as 6 tabbed sections, blank pages, adhesive labels, wine glossary, measures, conversions, and more! It also makes the perfect gift for any wine lover. Meaures 5in x 8.25in.

Journal Includes:

  • 6 themed sections to fill in: Sparkling, White, Rose, Red, Fortified/Sweet, and Spirits
  • 6 tabbed sections to personalize
  • 10 blank pages for notes and thoughts
  • 202 adhesive labels for customizing
  • Wine glossary, measures and conversions
  • 3 bookmark ribbons
  • Double expandable inner pocket
  • Elastic closure

Le Creuset Wine Cooler Sleeve
List.Description:
This wine cooler sleeve from Le Creuset is supreme. It can be used on the go to maintain a wine bottle's optimal temperature or used at home with its sleak, modern look. Simply put the cooler in your freezer until cold, then remove and slip over a wine bottle. The cooler will keep standard-size wine bottles chilled for hours. Sleeve fits all 75cl wine bottles, including still and sparkling wine bottles.

Wine not included.

Winerd: The Wine Tasting Game That Crushes Grape Fears
List.Description:
Wine tasting + wine trivia = major fun! This exciting board game tests everyone's wine knowledge with each sip. To start the game, taste three different wines, write down their names and where they are produced. Note the aromas, the colors, and the tastes. When a player lands on a blind tasting space, take a sip of one of the wines and try to remember which one it is. Land on a wine label space and answer trivia questions like "Why are wine bottles stored on their sides?" and "What grape is used predominantly for Beaujolais?" Are you a wine nerd?

Game Includes:

  • Trivia cards (285 questions)
  • Notepad
  • 4 tasting cards
  • Game board
  • 4 wine cork game pieces
  • 1 die
